spirit:vendorExtensions.actel-cc:description: The system services are system controller actions initiated by asynchronous events from the master in the FPGA fabric or external User Interface corresponding to each service. CoreSysServices soft IP provides access to the system services. The CoreSysServices soft IP communicates with the COMM_BLK through one of the FIC interfaces. The CoreSysServices handles the system services grouped together into following groups of services: Device and Design Information Services Flash*Freeze Service Programming Service Cryptographic Services PUF Services DPA-Resistant Key-Tree Services Non-Deterministic Random Bit Generator (NRBG) Services Zeroization Service Digest Check Service Unrecognized Command Response
